items.description:
RaenaMix is an alternate version of RaemuMix that focuses on a 2D anime style.

⬇Please share your cool creation below⬇

If you enjoy my work and want to support me, you can buy me a coffee at Ko-fi

Suggested Prompt

Prompt :

(masterpiece, best quality), intricate details,

Negative prompt :

(worst quality, low quality:1.4), monochrome, zombie, (interlocked fingers:1.2), fcNeg-neg

Embeddings : FastnegativeV2, fcNeg

Recommended Settings

  • Sampler : Euler a

  • Steps : 20+

  • CFG Scale : 7+

  • Clip Skip : 2

  • ENSD : 31337

  • Vae : included, set it to auto

  • Resolution : 512x912 (this is just my preference), Standard 512x768

Hires.fix Settings

  • Denoising : 0.25~0.45

Optional

  • Set eta to 0.667

  • Extension !ADetailer can help to fix face if its too far

Give 5 rating and a review if you like it, its motivation for me to improve more

items.name: Marisol Yotta
items.description:
A rquest I received through my website.

Marisol Ortiz, aka Marisol Yotta, is an American OnlyFans model and social media influencer.

This is step 120 of a TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (my0tta:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Sicilian Playing Cards
items.description:
This is a Lora for the sicilian playing cards (Carte Siciliane)

use carteSiciliane in the prompt, and then you can add the seed of the card (mazze, spade, oro, coppe).
this model tends to make Coppe cards more than other seeds.
You can also use the value of the card (asso, due, tre, quattro, cinque, sei, sette) or the figure represented (donna, cavallo, re).

The model tends to do way better at making the characters rather than a specific value for a card. (for instance, if you write Re it's likely you'll get the king, but if you write Tre, it doesn't always produce a 3)

items.name: C.A.G. - Coinmaker
items.description:
Hi again! Long time no see.

Welcome to Coinmaker. Coinmaker is my second "concept art generator" here. This time I trained a coin-asset-generator LORA for SDXL 0.9 that will makes easier, more fun and aesthetics the coin assets creation for videogames, renders, etc. It's specially useful for 3D projecting and extrude-modelling in 3D softwares. So that's why instead of having an small coin it will generate a big coin to be able to extrude all details (as requested)... also he told me that could be used for logo/shield but that's not the main purpose.


Token is c01n.


IMPORTANT: This was tested under ComfyUI, I don't have any idea how it will go with Automatic1111. I strongly recommend you to use ComfyUI if you want good results and most important, if you want the same settings I used just drag any image into the ComfyUI and it will show the full workflow, it seems CivitAI converted all samples to JPG so instead of dragging the images (if the workflow is not appearing):


https://huggingface.co/datasets/davizca87/C01nWorkflow/tree/main <- LOAD it via Json file in Comfyui


How to prompt and which values to use?
********************************************
- The LORA works perfectly with values from 1-1.2 and bellow even IMO it's better to stay at 1 (you can see Clip and Model 1/1 values).
- Resolutions 768x768 and 1024x1024 onwards, very important the ratio is a SQUARE.

- You should prompt with a little description of what you want having in mind it was trained to have a clean background and a type of metal. This is just for an specific purpose but currently support 4 metals (gold, silver, bronze, ancient).

- Structure as: "photograph/design/artwork of a (type of metal) c01n with a concept-you-want inscription over black background". Black background makes cleaner creations while inscription even optional push forward the trained aesthetics.

This LORA is good for
**********************

- 3D renders of coins of different type and styles. <- Main purporse
- Variations of a lot of coins inner properties. ex: bloody, melt, drip, damaged...
- Concepts engraved in the coins. Some may need prompt tweaking
- Realistic or semi-realistic results.

This LORA is not to be used for:
**********************************

- Moving the coins between or across the scenes or putting them inside any recipient.
- Making ANY figure/character engraved, some won't work. Thats' AI limitations.
- Fill an scenery of coins.


Massive thanks to the original user who requested this LORA and let me upload this to CivitAI so all could enjoy. Hope you all enjoy this and thanks for the continue support in our Patreon


Have fun! David.

items.name: Kirk Douglas Lora
items.description:
I am Loratacus!

Be nice, have fun!

Kirk Douglas (born Issur Danielovitch; December 9, 1916 – February 5, 2020) was an American actor and filmmaker. After an impoverished childhood, he made his film debut in The Strange Love of Martha Ivers (1946) with Barbara Stanwyck. Douglas soon developed into a leading box-office star throughout the 1950s, known for serious dramas, including westerns and war films. During his career, he appeared in more than 90 films and was known for his explosive acting style. He was named by the American Film Institute the 17th-greatest male star of Classic Hollywood cinema.

Douglas played an unscrupulous boxing hero in Champion (1949), which brought him his first nomination for the Academy Award for Best Actor. His other early films include Out of the Past (1947); Young Man with a Horn (1950), playing opposite Lauren Bacall and Doris Day; Ace in the Hole (1951); and Detective Story (1951), for which he received a Golden Globe nomination. He received his second Oscar nomination for his dramatic role in The Bad and the Beautiful (1952), opposite Lana Turner, and earned his third for portraying Vincent van Gogh in Lust for Life (1956), a role for which he won the Golden Globe for the Best Actor in a Drama. He also starred with James Mason in the adventure 20,000 Leagues Under the Sea (1954), a large box-office hit.

In September 1949, he established Bryna Productions, which began producing films as varied as Paths of Glory (1957) and Spartacus (1960). In those two films, he collaborated with the then-relatively unknown director Stanley Kubrick, taking lead roles in both films. Douglas helped to break the Hollywood blacklist by having Dalton Trumbo write Spartacus with an official on-screen credit.[1] He produced and starred in Lonely Are the Brave (1962) and Seven Days in May (1964), the latter opposite Burt Lancaster, with whom he made seven films. In 1963, he starred in the Broadway play One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest, a story that he purchased and later gave to his son Michael Douglas, who turned it into an Oscar-winning film. Douglas continued acting into the 1980s, appearing in such films as Saturn 3 (1980), The Man from Snowy River (1980), Tough Guys (1986), a reunion with Lancaster, and in the television version of Inherit the Wind (1988) plus in an episode of Touched by an Angel in 2002, for which he received his third nomination for an Emmy Award.

As an actor and philanthropist, Douglas received an Academy Honorary Award for Lifetime Achievement and the Presidential Medal of Freedom. As an author, he wrote ten novels and memoirs. After barely surviving a helicopter crash in 1991 and then suffering a stroke in 1996, he focused on renewing his spiritual and religious life. He lived with his second wife, producer Anne Buydens, until his death in 2020. A centenarian, Douglas was one of the last surviving stars of the film industry's Golden Age.[2]

items.name: Sims CAS Concept LORA
items.description:
A lora trained on the Sims 4 CAS.

Trigger Word: simscas, [view], [left, right]

CFG: 5 (have no tried other CFGs)

Weight: 1, though others use 0.5-0.8

Resolution: Trained and Tested on 512x896

Checkpoint: Tested on Epicrealism (my fav checkpoint tbh)

Views: You can choose between: Front View, Side View Left, Side View Right, Back View

Front view works best. The side views work the least.

Gender: Just put man or woman somewhere in the prompt.

Weight(body weight, not lora weight): The training images were randomized body types, so specifying weight works well.

Skin Color: Specify the race and skin color you want. (IE: African, Black Skin). This somewhat works, but dark skin tones are difficult to get to generate, even though around half the training images were dark skin tones.

Characters: Sometimes character LORAs make the character have purple skin, but other times it works pretty well.

Clothes: Clothing LORAs work surprisingly well. Given they are full body generations, sometimes the clothes are under-detailed.

The example images include prompts and examples of using Characters and LORAs.

items.name: Ely Cosplay (eeelyeee) - Flexible Lora
items.description:
Lora Goal:

This lora aims to generate cosplayer Ely in any outfit/hairstyle. Great for controlnet or just normal gen. This is done by including over a dozen different cosplays with multiple hair styles, hair color,, eye colors and outfits. The default is brown hair, brown eyes.

Outfits:

Each picture example with long prompt is trained on at least 2 pictures of ely wearing the outfit so they are lora specific and can be reliably generated by copying the relevant tokens found in the metadata of the images. But because of the sheer variety, none of them will interfere with outfits not in the lora, I included some examples with shorter prompts at the end to showcase this.

Flaws:

The only flaw would be that bangs require a bit of effort to remove because they are always there in every picture she has. But I included an image showing it (pure work of fiction, she has no forehead) with the metadata to help remove the bangs (negative prompts (bangs:1.4)) and (forehead:1.2) in positive prompt.

Naturally upside down and completely sideways faces are no good for most Loras since it'd be weird to train those kind of pictures for one character and this one is no exception. Same with super close up face portraits, it makes the eyes blurry since most pictures are upper body or full body.

Because of images where her hands are near her face, adetailer will generated random dismembered fingers near the chin, to avoid this, use (hands,fingers:1.4) in adetailer negative, but it's a minority of images so it rarely occurs.

The training:

Was trained on chilloutmix which I found has the most similar realistic asian faces to hers. I've tested it on Majicmix as well and it will work but that model tends to make her look more korean than she is. 74 images, lots of different angles and poses. 22 repeats, 8 epochs. 768x resolution so you can generate at 768x768 or even 768x1024 which I use a lot.

My workflow:

I used 512x768 for the examples but I often like to use 768x1024 especially with controlnet to give it more pixels to work with.

And I'll use adetailer with the settings in the examples for much better faces. Euler a 20 steps gives great results, but can be random, DPM++ 2S a Karras is more predictable but requires 30 steps for solid results so I use Euler a 20 steps mostly.

You can use png info on my images to send the settings over except for enabling use seperate width/height on adetailer, it's always off at first so you have to turn it on, using 512x512 will give best results in my experience. 768x is sharper but less details for adetailer. 5 cfg is also important as the default 7 cfg can often cause burned look with artifacts.

I like to use perfectworldv4 because it often resembles how Ely displays herself while cosplaying with colorful hair, eyes and clothes.

Outfits that civitai won't allow:

Apparently some of her cosplays are too lewd to allow so I'll post the prompts for them here if you want to gen it yourself. These are what danbooru tagged the original photos.

Police woman: <lora:elyee:0.9> 3ly33, long hair, skirt, shirt, red eyes, gloves, hat, cleavage, hair between eyes, sitting, underwear, white shirt, white hair, pantyhose, black gloves, belt, black skirt, bra, uniform, torn clothes, black pantyhose, crossed legs, black bra, peaked cap, pencil skirt, cuffs, torn pantyhose, half gloves, handcuffs, police, police uniform, policewoman

Chinese dress: <lora:elyee:0.9>3ly33, long hair, bangs, dress, holding, cleavage, twintails, jewelry, sitting, very long hair, earrings, indoors, hair bun, white dress, bracelet, aqua eyes, clothing cutout, double bun, aqua hair, chinese clothes, cleavage cutout, china dress, hand fan, side slit, beads, lantern, holding fan, paper fan, paper lantern, lattice

items.description:
LoRA trained on Sylas from League of Legends

requested by: @slayyeraw

please wait with your request until i finished the remaining ones (Super Galaxy Nidalee, Zed)

tags: sylas \(league of legends\), 1boy, male focus, topless male, shackles, chain

female sylas: sylas \(league of legends\), 1girl, crop top, shackles, chain, long hair

anime: YabaL_Mix - V5, Cetus-Mix, Kawaii Realistic Anime Mix

2,5D: ERA_09 - v1.0 | Stable Diffusion Checkpoint | Civitai, Aniverse - Aniverse V1.1, DarkSun

realistic: Paragon V1.0

negative embeddings: Fast Negative Embedding v2

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models & 2,5D), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras(euler a for img2img upscaling) from time to time im also using DPM++ 2M alt Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 2

  • Upscaler : GitHub - pkuliyi2015/multidiffusion-upscaler-for-automatic1111 4x-UltraSharp(for 2,5D & realistic), 4xAnimesharp(for anime)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8 and 1)

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

If you want to autocomplete the tags & trigger im using, I recommend using Booru style tag autocompletion for AUTOMATIC1111's Stable Diffusion web UI

For full body shots i recommend using: ComfyUI Impact Pack

or the a1111 alternative GitHub - Bing-su/adetailer
